ightful stop at las Garitas, a local restaurant well recognized by locals and foreigners. Here, you can savor regional cuisine and start your day with a hearty meal before heading towards our first destination, the mesmerizing Balandra Beach. Here, soak up the sun and capture beautiful images of the emblematic mushroom-shaped rock that has become a symbol of La Paz.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"https://cabodrivers.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/roca_hongo_balandra.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-83 size-full\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our next stop is the tranquil Coromuel Beach, where you can enjoy more sun, sand, and sea. Post this relaxing beach visit, we head to a scenic restaurant on the beautiful La Paz boardwalk. Here, take in breathtaking views of the sunset while indulging in a leisurely hour-and-a-half-long lunch.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The tour continues to the renowned The Velvet Box Jewelry La Paz. Gain insights about the iconic La Paz pearls and browse their exquisite collection of jewelry pieces. This part of the tour concludes around 3:00-3:30pm, marking the end of our La Paz journey.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":84,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"https://cabodrivers.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/malecon_perla.jpg\" alt=\"Monument to la perla of La Paz\" class=\"wp-image-84\" title=\"A monument image to la Perla of La Paz\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From there, we proceed to Todos Santos, a magical town known for the famous Hotel California, where you can shop for local sweets and souvenirs. It\'s an extraordinary day filled with the best of Baja California Sur\'s culture, cuisine, and captivating landscapes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -